What is APR?

Annual Percentage Rate (APR) is a measure of the cost of borrowing money, expressed as a percentage. It includes the interest rate and any additional fees or charges associated with the loan over a year. APR helps consumers compare different loan offers by providing a standardized, easy-to-understand rate. By law, lenders are required to disclose the APR when advertising consumer loans. This way, borrowers can make more informed decisions about which loan is best for them.Can you write a poem about APR?

